22:00.487 --> 22:02.422
This is really hard right now.
(laughs)

22:02.555 --> 22:04.691
-You don't seem fine.
-(sobs)

22:04.824 --> 22:07.560
I'm so proud of you.

22:08.595 --> 22:10.096
(sobs)

22:10.229 --> 22:12.264
I love you.

22:12.399 --> 22:13.265
Uh, okay.

22:13.400 --> 22:14.934
(laughs)

22:15.067 --> 22:17.604
You're the light of my life.

22:17.737 --> 22:19.238
CLAIRE:
Oh. (sniffling)

22:19.372 --> 22:20.239
Okay. (laughs)

22:20.373 --> 22:21.908
(Claire sighs)

22:23.242 --> 22:25.044
Thanks for helping us
pack the car.

22:25.177 --> 22:26.312
SCOTT:
I'm sorry.

22:26.446 --> 22:28.615
I didn't realize
you guys were done already.

22:30.082 --> 22:31.551
Be nice to Mom.

22:31.684 --> 22:34.086
And please respond to my texts.

22:34.220 --> 22:35.822
I will. Don't worry about it.

22:35.955 --> 22:39.392
And, um... I-I'll come
visit you at some point.

22:40.427 --> 22:41.293
(smacks lips)

22:41.428 --> 22:42.829
Okay. All right.

22:42.962 --> 22:44.230
-Yeah.
-(sighs)

22:44.363 --> 22:45.998
-I love you.
-I love you, too.

22:46.132 --> 22:47.099
(sniffles)

22:47.233 --> 22:49.869
-MARGIE: Fly.
-(laughs)

22:51.571 --> 22:52.972
(whimpers)

22:53.105 --> 22:54.807
(car door closes)

22:54.941 --> 22:56.142
(engine starts)

22:57.944 --> 22:59.446
(over stereo):
* Keep on hoping we'll eat *

22:59.579 --> 23:01.448
-* Cake by the ocean *
-(Claire whoops)

23:01.581 --> 23:03.583
-* Talk to me, baby... *
-(music fades)

23:13.059 --> 23:14.494
SCOTT (quietly):
Hey.

23:14.627 --> 23:16.663
(chuckles softly)
Hey.

23:16.796 --> 23:18.798
Uh...

23:18.931 --> 23:21.601
I was thinking of finally
seeing that Game of Thrones.

23:21.734 --> 23:23.603
Should I binge it?

23:23.736 --> 23:25.171
Oh, it's a,
it's a pretty violent show.

23:25.304 --> 23:27.006
You sure you could watch that?

23:27.139 --> 23:29.476
I work in an emergency room.

23:29.609 --> 23:30.710
Right, yeah.

23:30.843 --> 23:33.212
So, you could probably handle
a good pillage.

23:33.345 --> 23:34.380
Yeah.

23:34.514 --> 23:37.216
Okay, well, maybe
I'll start watching it.

23:37.349 --> 23:38.851
-Yeah.
-You watch it with me?

23:38.985 --> 23:42.989
Um, well, I actually just kind
of finished it, so I-I don't--

23:43.122 --> 23:45.492
It's really fresh in my mind,
so I-I would probably...

23:45.625 --> 23:46.959
-Okay.
-I can watch some of them.

23:47.093 --> 23:49.629
Uh, I don't think I can watch
all of them again, but...

23:49.762 --> 23:51.363
-Well...
-I'll see you later, then.

23:51.498 --> 23:53.365
All right.

23:53.500 --> 23:55.367
Uh, are you okay?

23:55.502 --> 23:58.337
Or... (grunts)

23:58.471 --> 23:59.539
Oh. Yeah?

23:59.672 --> 24:00.540
-Come on.
-(sniffles)

24:00.673 --> 24:02.241
Uh, it's, it-it's...

24:02.374 --> 24:03.843
It's okay. It's--

24:03.976 --> 24:06.078
I-I'm here. Uh, I'm here.

24:06.212 --> 24:08.314
Don't-don't worry about it.

24:08.447 --> 24:09.448
-She's, you know...
-(sobs)

24:09.582 --> 24:11.584
Well, she's only, like,
45 minutes away,

24:11.718 --> 24:14.621
and she'll-she'll probably
call in, like, five minutes.

24:16.288 --> 24:17.389
-(sniffles)
-But, hey.

24:17.524 --> 24:19.726
You still got me, right?

24:21.193 --> 24:22.729
Yeah.

24:26.966 --> 24:28.034
Oh, shit.

24:28.167 --> 24:29.902
-(laughing)
-Hey, hey!

24:31.337 --> 24:33.940
OSCAR: See, you got to
hold it like this.

24:34.073 --> 24:35.675
TARA:
Let's see. Oh.

24:35.808 --> 24:38.144
-Oh, yeah!
-Oh!

24:39.178 --> 24:40.680
Hey, hey, wait. Hey, hey, guys.

24:40.813 --> 24:42.682
Look, look.

24:42.815 --> 24:43.916
You can't be here, man.

24:44.050 --> 24:45.618
-Y-You got to go.
-KELSEY: Why?

24:45.752 --> 24:47.920
GUARD: It's private property,
that's why.

24:48.054 --> 24:50.256
It's an abandoned orphanage.
Why can't we be here?

24:50.389 --> 24:51.558
RICHIE:
Who gives a shit, man?

24:51.691 --> 24:52.859
What are you doing here?

24:52.992 --> 24:54.426
You fucking protecting
the ghosts of dead orphans?

24:54.561 --> 24:57.429
Look, fat Kanye,
shut your damn mouth.

24:57.564 --> 24:59.966
I'll be back in five minutes
for you assholes.

25:00.099 --> 25:02.234
If you're still here,
I'm calling the cops, period.

25:02.368 --> 25:04.537
You better get the cops, man,
'cause you're a fake cop.

25:04.671 --> 25:06.305
-You need the real ones.
-GUARD: Motherfuckers.

25:06.438 --> 25:08.407
-Fuck all of y'all.
-IGOR: I feel bad.

25:08.541 --> 25:09.876
We-we were a little too mean.

25:10.009 --> 25:11.477
-SCOTT: Yeah.
-He's nice.

25:11.611 --> 25:12.912
Yeah, he's a really good guy.

25:13.045 --> 25:17.449
See, that guy-- that is what is
wrong with Staten Island.

25:17.584 --> 25:20.486
We don't get any cool people
from any of the other boroughs.

25:20.620 --> 25:21.854
No one comes here.

25:21.988 --> 25:24.090
We're stuck with the
fucking pricks that live here.

25:24.223 --> 25:25.758
You're talking about us.

25:25.892 --> 25:27.126
Right in front of us.

25:27.259 --> 25:28.127
KELSEY:
Yeah, kinda.

25:28.260 --> 25:29.796
I mean, no one comes here.

25:29.929 --> 25:31.598
There's no flow of people.
That guy's, like, 200.

25:31.731 --> 25:32.999
We've known him
since we were six.

25:33.132 --> 25:34.901
Why can't we be cool
like Brooklyn?

25:35.034 --> 25:36.836
There's no reason we shouldn't
be cool like Brooklyn.

25:36.969 --> 25:39.338
We got amazing views.
It's close to the city.

25:39.471 --> 25:41.641
It's cheap. Nice people.
It makes no sense.

25:41.774 --> 25:44.110
We're, like, the only place
that New Jersey looks down on.

25:44.243 --> 25:46.979
-You could see the garbage dump
from space. -(Tara laughs)

25:47.113 --> 25:48.748
This place is
never gonna change.

25:48.881 --> 25:49.982
No, it happened to
the Meatpacking District,

25:50.116 --> 25:51.183
the Village.

25:51.317 --> 25:53.119
Brooklyn used to be
a fucking shithole.

25:53.252 --> 25:54.253
We are next.

25:54.386 --> 25:55.554
I'm gonna take
my civil service test.

25:55.688 --> 25:57.757
I'm gonna work in the city,
in city planning.

25:57.890 --> 25:59.926
You watch, this place is gonna
be like fucking Williamsburg

26:00.059 --> 26:02.428
-in ten years. -RICHIE: No, all
right? No. Nobody wants that.

26:02.561 --> 26:04.697
Why do you want to work in
the city and do city planning?

26:04.831 --> 26:05.698
That sounds so boring.

26:05.832 --> 26:07.199
I feel like Brooklyn is better.

26:07.333 --> 26:08.801
I dated a guy
that lived in Brooklyn.

26:08.935 --> 26:09.936
He was a mixologist.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.538
He made ice cubes out of milk.

26:12.672 --> 26:14.707
-He was so classy.
-OSCAR: Shut up!

26:14.841 --> 26:16.643
I love Staten Island.

26:16.776 --> 26:17.877
It's amazing.

26:18.010 --> 26:19.712
And people are gonna
see it soon, trust me.

26:19.846 --> 26:21.313
SCOTT:
Well, if you love it so much,

26:21.447 --> 26:22.849
why don't you let me
tattoo it on you?

26:22.982 --> 26:24.851
No, I'm not gonna let you
tattoo me again.

26:24.984 --> 26:25.852
Fine.

26:25.985 --> 26:28.988
Well, I need somebody to tattoo.

26:29.121 --> 26:30.556
I'm, I-I'm running out of...

26:30.690 --> 26:31.891
Come on, Rich.
What about you, man?

26:32.024 --> 26:34.026
-Don't even look at me, dude.
-Why?

26:34.160 --> 26:35.895
Your work is mad inconsistent.

26:36.028 --> 26:37.329
Obama ain't right.

26:37.463 --> 26:38.698
SCOTT:
I got the eyes wrong, okay?

26:38.831 --> 26:39.966
RICHIE:
He's not right.

26:40.099 --> 26:42.068
All right, man,
this has hurt me, all right?

26:42.201 --> 26:43.670
I don't have
any black friends anymore.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.638
I can't go to
a barber shop no more.

26:45.772 --> 26:48.474
You got Obama wrong.
Ain't nothing worse than that.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.743
What about you, Igor?
You want a dragon or something?

26:50.877 --> 26:52.244
Oh, I love your tattoos.

26:52.378 --> 26:53.479
My brother?

26:53.612 --> 26:54.914
It's a spitting image.

26:55.047 --> 26:56.315
-SCOTT: Yeah. It's one of
the best. -It's my favorite.

26:56.448 --> 26:57.717
No, no, no, no.
This is my favorite.

26:57.850 --> 26:59.085
Oh, you killed that.

26:59.218 --> 27:00.419
-Yeah, I really worked hard
on the eyes. -Just...

27:00.552 --> 27:02.655
He's so cute.
I love his butthole.

27:02.789 --> 27:04.523
It reminds me that I have
a belly button.

27:04.657 --> 27:06.492
-So, I'm good.
-Yeah, I got to go.

27:06.625 --> 27:09.528
(chuckles): Watching you beg
to give tattoos is too sad.

27:09.662 --> 27:11.931
(laughs):
And that's freaking me out.

27:12.064 --> 27:13.565
-(tattoo gun buzzing)
-SCOTT: We're almost done.

27:13.700 --> 27:14.834
-(Igor groans)
-Almost.

27:14.967 --> 27:16.769
(panting sharply)

27:16.903 --> 27:18.504
(seabirds squawking in distance)

27:18.637 --> 27:19.872
All right.

27:20.006 --> 27:21.540
-You're all done.
-That looks really good.

27:21.674 --> 27:23.175
Yeah, I mean, I wish

27:23.309 --> 27:25.011
you'd let me do
something cooler, but yeah.

27:25.144 --> 27:26.779
Oh, fuck no.
That hurts so bad.

27:26.913 --> 27:29.181
-Another dumb tattoo. -SCOTT:
Yeah, but I-I like the pain.

27:29.315 --> 27:31.517
The-the pain is the whole point
of getting tattoos.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.052
Don't you just love
when you're getting tattooed,

27:33.185 --> 27:34.854
and it hits the bone
and pinches a nerve,

27:34.987 --> 27:36.022
and you're like...
(pained groan)

27:36.155 --> 27:37.857
I'm not a fan of the pain.

27:37.990 --> 27:39.358
You shouldn't let him
do it to you, all right?

27:39.491 --> 27:40.559
He's inconsistent.

27:40.693 --> 27:42.561
OSCAR:
I think that tattoo's dumb.

27:42.695 --> 27:44.463
Y'all should've told me
when you saw the design.

27:44.596 --> 27:45.664
It says, "Unfollow me."

27:45.798 --> 27:47.199
You don't even have
that many followers.

27:47.333 --> 27:49.435
Carla follows me.

27:49.568 --> 27:51.037
-Bro, she's imaginary.
-OSCAR: Carla not real.

27:51.170 --> 27:52.371
Carla's not real, dude.

27:52.504 --> 27:54.406
RICHIE: How many times
do we have to say this?

27:54.540 --> 27:56.242
-SCOTT: She's not real.
-(insect buzzing)

27:56.375 --> 27:57.710
I hate bugs, dawg.

27:57.844 --> 27:58.878
I'm a gangster!

27:59.011 --> 28:00.246
SCOTT:
No, that's a bee, bro!

28:00.379 --> 28:02.448
OSCAR:
There's a kid down there.

28:02.581 --> 28:03.983
-Yo, kid!
-(chuckles): Oh, yo.

28:04.116 --> 28:05.952
-Yo, kid, what's up?
-Oh, shit, there is a kid.

28:06.085 --> 28:07.619
What are you doing?

28:07.754 --> 28:09.388
You hanging out on the beach?
Come here, come here.

28:09.521 --> 28:11.623
Don't-don't be shy.
No stranger danger here.

28:11.758 --> 28:12.892
I'm not gonna touch you.

28:13.025 --> 28:14.260
-What's up, pal?
-What are you doing?

28:14.393 --> 28:15.494
I'm looking for my friend.

28:15.627 --> 28:16.896
(mocking):
"Looking for my friend."

28:17.029 --> 28:19.465
-(Richie laughs)
-You want to be friends with us?

28:19.598 --> 28:21.734
We're the good guys, right?

28:21.868 --> 28:22.935
-You can hang out with us, pal.
-Come on.

28:23.069 --> 28:24.937
Let me get some of that.
Put it right there.

28:25.071 --> 28:26.272
-(fists bump)
-(imitates explosion)

28:26.405 --> 28:28.640
-Ho! (laughs)
-You gang.

28:28.775 --> 28:29.976
Part of the gang.

28:30.109 --> 28:31.443
SCOTT:
Gang.

28:31.577 --> 28:32.611
What's that?

28:32.745 --> 28:33.846
Uh, it's a tattoo gun.

28:33.980 --> 28:35.281
I was giving the homeys tattoos.

28:35.414 --> 28:37.483
-I want a tattoo.
-(laughter)

28:37.616 --> 28:39.518
-You're a tough guy?
-SCOTT: Really?

28:39.651 --> 28:41.821
-Sure, young guy.
You want a tattoo? -Yeah.

28:41.954 --> 28:44.123
Dude, kid wants a tattoo.
That's my guy right there.

28:44.256 --> 28:45.324
Bro, you-you can't
give him a tattoo.

28:45.457 --> 28:46.759
-He's a little kid.
-Yeah, there we go.

28:46.893 --> 28:48.660
-You want a tattoo? -Bro,
I got to practice on something.

28:48.795 --> 28:50.096
-Yeah.
-He seems old enough.

28:50.229 --> 28:51.798
-OSCAR: You a tough guy?
-Yeah.

28:51.931 --> 28:52.999
-You a badass.
-(laughter)

28:53.132 --> 28:54.466
Come on,
show those muscles, kid.

28:54.600 --> 28:56.168
-Come on. Both arms, both arms.
-RICHIE: Yeah, there you go.

28:56.302 --> 28:58.170
-Put 'em up. -SCOTT: You got
tickets to the gun show?

28:58.304 --> 28:59.939
-There it is. There it is.
-All right. -There we go.

29:00.072 --> 29:01.440
-What's your name?
-Harold.

29:01.573 --> 29:02.708
I'm-a call you Harry.

29:02.842 --> 29:04.276
Don't. It's Harold.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.045
-Oh.
-RICHIE (chuckles): Okay.

29:06.178 --> 29:07.980
-Hell yeah.
-I like this kid.

29:08.114 --> 29:09.715
I need him in my life.

29:09.849 --> 29:11.117
He has structure.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.318
(lighter clicks)

29:12.451 --> 29:14.053
Guys, I don't think
that's a good idea.

29:14.186 --> 29:16.889
I mean... we don't listen
to anything you say.

29:17.023 --> 29:19.325
-Yeah. -Yeah, I mean, why do
you even try to give us advice?

29:19.458 --> 29:21.460
SCOTT: So, what do you want
a tattoo of?

29:21.593 --> 29:22.461
The Punisher.

29:22.594 --> 29:24.163
-The Punisher?
-RICHIE: Okay.

29:24.296 --> 29:25.798
-That's tough, man.
-SCOTT: All right.

29:25.932 --> 29:28.300
He could've said anything.
He said The Punisher.

29:28.434 --> 29:30.336
Oh, yeah, I could do that.
Is that it?

29:30.469 --> 29:31.570
Yeah, that's him.

29:31.703 --> 29:33.806
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

29:33.940 --> 29:36.742
Do I have your legal permission
to do this?

29:36.876 --> 29:38.477
-Yes.
-That's good enough for me.

29:38.610 --> 29:40.079
-How about you guys?
-OSCAR: Holds up in court.

29:40.212 --> 29:41.247
You guys heard it. All right.

29:41.380 --> 29:42.849
Yo, he can't get consent.
He's ten.

29:42.982 --> 29:46.185
Now, hold still, okay?
'Cause it is permanent.

29:46.318 --> 29:49.021
Yo, guys. Stop.
Stop, stop, stop.

29:49.155 --> 29:50.722
-Put your game face on.
-SCOTT: Don't worry, dude.

29:50.857 --> 29:53.325
This will just be on you
for the rest of your life.

29:53.459 --> 29:55.261
-(tattoo gun buzzing)
-There you go.

29:55.394 --> 29:56.929
-Look at you, tough guy.
-RICHIE: There you go.

29:57.063 --> 29:59.098
-(screams) I don't want
to do it! -Uh...

29:59.231 --> 30:00.566
-I don't wanna!
-Well, I got to finish it.

30:00.699 --> 30:02.101
-Now there's just a line.
-OSCAR: Calm down, man.

30:02.234 --> 30:03.903
-You're gonna look stupid. Sit
back down. Relax. -Calm down.

30:04.036 --> 30:05.437
-Sit down. Do it.
-Relax.

30:05.571 --> 30:06.906
-RICHIE: Whoa! Hey!
-Hey! -Hey!

30:07.039 --> 30:08.740
-Hey, run! Run, kid!
-Hey!

30:08.875 --> 30:10.776
Run, little man! Run!

30:10.910 --> 30:12.611
Run!

30:12.744 --> 30:14.246
Goddamn it.

30:14.380 --> 30:15.948
I fucking believed
in that kid, man.

30:16.082 --> 30:19.551
He seemed so tough at first,
uh, but then immediately wasn't.

30:19.685 --> 30:21.420
That's why I don't fuck
with millennials, dude.

30:21.553 --> 30:24.723
Again, we are the millennials.

30:24.857 --> 30:26.725
He keeps saying that, but
I don't know what that means.

30:26.859 --> 30:29.761
I regret my friendship
with you guys.

30:29.896 --> 30:32.598
(heavy knocking)

30:41.507 --> 30:43.209
Yeah, hello.
My name's Raymond Bishop.

30:43.342 --> 30:45.411
This is my son, Harold.
Say hello, Harold.

30:45.544 --> 30:46.745
I'm sorry.

30:46.879 --> 30:48.915
What's going on?

30:49.048 --> 30:50.582
Well, it seems your son
was down in the woods

30:50.716 --> 30:52.885
giving out free tattoos, and
my son was one of his victims.

30:53.019 --> 30:54.887
What?
Well, I-I don't understand.

30:55.021 --> 30:57.489
How do you know it was my son?
How'd you get this address?

30:57.623 --> 30:59.825
I have my ways.
Believe me, I have my ways.

30:59.959 --> 31:01.027
Are you a cop?

31:01.160 --> 31:02.728
No, I'm a fireman, okay?
I work for a living.

31:02.861 --> 31:03.996
Look at this.
Do you believe this?

31:04.130 --> 31:05.797
You see that there?
See that line?

31:05.932 --> 31:07.666
I don't know if you
burn these off or what,

31:07.799 --> 31:08.935
but we're taking care of this

31:09.068 --> 31:10.302
and you're paying for it,
you understand me?

31:10.436 --> 31:12.638
-I don't know what this is.
-Scott! Oh.

31:12.771 --> 31:14.306
I am-- I'm so sorry.

31:14.440 --> 31:15.908
I-I-I...

31:16.042 --> 31:17.977
There's an aesthetic laser
at the hospital where I work,

31:18.110 --> 31:19.946
and it can completely remove it.

31:20.079 --> 31:21.313
Uh, I get a discount.

31:21.447 --> 31:22.781
I'm-I'm gonna pay
for the whole thing.

31:22.915 --> 31:24.616
I don't know what I'm saying.
I'm-- I feel terrible.

31:24.750 --> 31:25.617
You should feel terrible!

31:25.751 --> 31:26.953
Look at that!

31:27.086 --> 31:28.955
-What's up? Oh, fuck.
-Ah, there he is.

31:29.088 --> 31:31.323
-You get your ass out here!
-Hey, he said he was 18.

31:31.457 --> 31:33.926
He looks like he's four,
you fucking moron! Sorry.

31:34.060 --> 31:35.928
-He consented!
-He's lying.

31:36.062 --> 31:37.696
-Harold, come on!
-RAY: Course he's lying!

31:37.829 --> 31:39.999
You can't have consent!
He's nine years old!

31:40.132 --> 31:41.633
Dad, let's go.
You're embarrassing me.

31:41.767 --> 31:42.701
We're not going anywhere, okay?

31:42.834 --> 31:43.802
He's just a little kid!

31:43.936 --> 31:45.004
What the fuck
is wrong with you?!

31:45.137 --> 31:46.605
Uh, he was roaming around
in the woods.

31:46.738 --> 31:48.174
He wanted a tattoo.
W-Where were you?

31:48.307 --> 31:49.942
I was at fucking work!

31:50.076 --> 31:51.177
-Fuck you! -Hey!
-Come out here!

31:51.310 --> 31:52.511
If I was you,
I'd shut your fucking mouth,

31:52.644 --> 31:53.712
because I can
call the cops right now

31:53.845 --> 31:54.913
and have your ass
