52:13.564 --> 52:14.465
a run for their money.

52:14.599 --> 52:17.668
These guys are all
on the job, too.

52:17.802 --> 52:19.437
The old ballbuster here--

52:19.570 --> 52:21.038
he's the senior man
of the house.

52:21.172 --> 52:23.040
Did you call me a senior?

52:23.174 --> 52:24.675
You're the one who's bald.

52:24.809 --> 52:26.444
Come on, Papa.
I'm just fucking around.

52:26.577 --> 52:27.845
Hey, you want a hot dog?

52:27.978 --> 52:30.381
Oh, no, I can't.
I, uh, I have Crohn's.

52:30.515 --> 52:31.916
What's that?

52:32.049 --> 52:34.452
It's, like, when the lining of
your stomach is all messed up,

52:34.585 --> 52:36.954
so it makes you shit
all the time.

52:37.087 --> 52:38.923
Oh, thanks for sharing.

52:40.491 --> 52:42.293
Next time, just say,
"I don't want a hot dog."

52:42.427 --> 52:43.994
All right, I'm just trying
to spread awareness.

52:45.029 --> 52:46.096
(crowd cheering)

52:46.231 --> 52:47.598
RAY:
There we go. There we go.

52:47.732 --> 52:50.368
-Nice hit. Nice hit.
-Looking good, guys.

52:50.501 --> 52:51.936
Way to hustle.

52:52.069 --> 52:53.137
STADIUM ANNOUNCER:
Number 26...

52:53.271 --> 52:55.573
Hey, uh...

52:55.706 --> 52:57.875
you ever think about
putting on the jacket?

52:59.377 --> 53:00.878
-(scoffs) No.
-What are you laughing about?

53:01.011 --> 53:04.249
'Cause it's
a stupid question, Ray.

53:04.382 --> 53:07.585
-What do you mean, stupid?
-It's fucking stupid.

53:07.718 --> 53:09.787
Would you ask the kids of that
teacher who blew up in space

53:09.920 --> 53:11.188
if they want to be an astronaut?

53:11.322 --> 53:13.658
Whoa, I don't think that lady
had any kids, though.

53:13.791 --> 53:16.060
Yeah, I'm sure she didn't
'cause she died in space.

53:16.193 --> 53:19.330
It's hard to have kids
when you're dead in space.

53:19.464 --> 53:22.667
Look, I-I could tell you
how I feel about firemen,

53:22.800 --> 53:24.502
but I-I don't think you guys
want to hear my opinion.

53:24.635 --> 53:26.437
-No, no, no, please tell us.
-RAY: No, no. No, no, no.

53:26.571 --> 53:28.439
-No. I want to hear it.
-You don't got to do this, man.

53:28.573 --> 53:29.807
-Come on.
-All right, no.

53:29.940 --> 53:31.309
-Yeah. Okay, how about this?
-Come on, you don't...

53:31.442 --> 53:33.143
Uh, if you're a fireman,
just don't have kids

53:33.278 --> 53:34.579
or a family at all, okay?

53:34.712 --> 53:36.414
So that way, you don't
fucking crush them

53:36.547 --> 53:39.149
when you don't come home
that one time, you know?

53:39.284 --> 53:40.618
And-and you're just so selfish.

53:40.751 --> 53:42.253
You just hang out
with your boys all day

53:42.387 --> 53:43.688
like it's a fucking frat house.

53:43.821 --> 53:45.990
Half the time, you're not even
putting out fires.

53:46.123 --> 53:49.093
You're just jerking off,
watching Scarface, okay?

53:49.226 --> 53:51.095
-All right, take it easy, man.
-No, I'm just saying.

53:51.228 --> 53:52.997
And it's wrong to tell a kid
that you're gonna be there

53:53.130 --> 53:54.399
for him for his whole
entire life.

53:54.532 --> 53:57.302
Yeah, but you miss graduation,
your birthdays, okay?

53:57.435 --> 53:58.869
Uh, my d-- my prom dances.

53:59.003 --> 54:01.672
That's a very mean thing
to do to children.

54:01.806 --> 54:02.873
And, uh, if you have a family,

54:03.007 --> 54:04.174
-y-you're an asshole.
-No, listen, no.

54:04.309 --> 54:05.476
Take it easy, take it easy.

54:05.610 --> 54:07.478
-Well, that's one way
to look at it. -Yeah.

54:07.612 --> 54:08.813
Tell that to my dad.

54:11.316 --> 54:15.286
Oh, but you can't,
'cause he's dead.

54:15.420 --> 54:17.488
-Anybody got a good response
to that? -(bat cracks)

54:17.622 --> 54:20.124
-(crowd cheering)
-Yeah!

54:20.257 --> 54:22.226
Again!

54:22.360 --> 54:23.328
Whoo!

54:23.461 --> 54:26.464
What a game.
What a game.

54:26.597 --> 54:28.666
So, what, I shouldn't have kids?

54:28.799 --> 54:30.535
No, you... you should have kids.

54:30.668 --> 54:31.836
I'm gonna have kids.

54:31.969 --> 54:33.371
You know, maybe
you should take a cue

54:33.504 --> 54:35.573
from your shirt, you know?
Smile.

54:35.706 --> 54:38.409
Lighten up.

54:38.543 --> 54:40.311
(chuckles)
That's actually kind of funny.

54:40.445 --> 54:41.912
Guy's all right.
Why can't you be more like him?

54:42.046 --> 54:43.348
He's all right.

54:43.481 --> 54:45.683
Why can't you not
embarrass me like this?

54:45.816 --> 54:47.418
I'm sorry.

54:47.552 --> 54:50.054
I'm sorry I embarrassed you
in front of your friends.

54:50.187 --> 54:51.689
(laughs)

54:53.724 --> 54:55.660
(quietly): And just-just
stick to your guns.

54:55.793 --> 54:57.061
All right? It'll be fine.

54:57.194 --> 54:58.228
Hey. Hey!

54:58.363 --> 54:59.263
Come on in.

54:59.397 --> 55:00.998
Come have breakfast with us.

55:01.131 --> 55:03.734
I made pancakes, and I made
the sausage that you like,

55:03.868 --> 55:04.769
an omelet.

55:04.902 --> 55:06.036
Come, come, come, come sit.

55:06.170 --> 55:08.205
RAY:
Man, these eggs are spectacular.

55:08.339 --> 55:10.341
With the onions and the peppers.

55:10.475 --> 55:13.243
I love it. I love it.
(sniffs)

55:14.745 --> 55:17.281
Did, uh, did he
sp-spend the night?

55:17.415 --> 55:18.916
MARGIE:
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

55:19.049 --> 55:20.418
He slept here.

55:20.551 --> 55:21.452
In this house.

55:21.586 --> 55:23.287
I'm an adult. I can do that.

55:23.421 --> 55:25.255
(chuckles)

55:25.390 --> 55:27.692
I-I need to talk to you
about something.

55:27.825 --> 55:29.093
Okay.

55:29.226 --> 55:30.895
I was thinking that it's time

55:31.028 --> 55:32.863
to think about
getting your own apartment.

55:32.997 --> 55:34.465
What?

55:34.599 --> 55:36.300
W-Why would you say that?

55:36.434 --> 55:38.068
Well...

55:39.904 --> 55:41.572
You are so awesome.

55:41.706 --> 55:45.576
And I think I've been there
for you too much.

55:45.710 --> 55:48.546
'Cause sometimes in life,
the thing that's motivating

55:48.679 --> 55:51.048
is when people don't have
that safety net.

55:51.181 --> 55:52.917
Right, right,
but I need that safety net

55:53.050 --> 55:54.318
'cause I don't have
my shit together.

55:54.452 --> 55:56.153
So, like, uh,
w-why are you doing this?

55:56.286 --> 55:57.555
Is this 'cause of him?

55:58.589 --> 56:00.157
No.

56:00.290 --> 56:02.960
It's just you're
24 years old now.

56:03.093 --> 56:06.764
24. I mean, Phelps had
a fistful of gold medals by 24.

56:06.897 --> 56:08.766
Why are you talking?

56:08.899 --> 56:11.235
I'm just giving you
some perspective, that's all.

56:11.368 --> 56:13.671
You know, Wayne Gretzky had,
like, 96 goals when he was 24.

56:13.804 --> 56:15.773
W-What?

56:15.906 --> 56:17.975
RAY: Roger Staubach
graduated West Point,

56:18.108 --> 56:21.245
won a Heisman Trophy,
fought in the Vietnam War,

56:21.378 --> 56:23.648
and then joined the Cowboys
by the time he was 24.

56:23.781 --> 56:26.851
I don't know who that is,
so, s-so who-who gives a fuck?

56:26.984 --> 56:29.153
I think that maybe
you're-you're ready

56:29.286 --> 56:31.155
and you just don't even know it.

56:31.288 --> 56:33.591
So, you're kicking me out?

56:33.724 --> 56:34.992
No, no.

56:35.125 --> 56:37.428
I just want you to get
your own apartment by summer.

56:37.562 --> 56:39.464
Right, so you're kicking me
out of the house.

56:39.597 --> 56:41.466
That's nine months from now.

56:41.599 --> 56:43.501
I mean, you-you could have
a baby in nine months.

56:43.634 --> 56:44.835
It's a long time.

56:44.969 --> 56:46.771
Are you moving in?
Are you trying to push me out?

56:46.904 --> 56:48.973
What, like, what did I do?
I-I thought we were cool.

56:49.106 --> 56:50.975
Scott, Scott, let's all
be adults here. Come on.

56:51.108 --> 56:53.511
Your mother has worked
very hard for a very long time.

56:53.644 --> 56:55.179
And I'm gonna retire
in a couple years,

56:55.312 --> 56:59.049
so things are gonna change
around here, but in a good way.

56:59.183 --> 57:01.486
I mean, w-we think you--
that you can do great things.

57:01.619 --> 57:02.953
Yeah, I know I'm gonna do
great things.

57:03.087 --> 57:05.523
But, like, I don't need you
to tell me that, like...

57:05.656 --> 57:06.857
This is-- What's going on?

57:06.991 --> 57:08.959
This is-- I-I...

57:09.093 --> 57:10.495
I don't like this.

57:10.628 --> 57:12.497
So, be that as it may,
(chuckles)

57:12.630 --> 57:14.499
until you leave--
which is gonna be good for you

57:14.632 --> 57:15.733
and it's gonna be motivating--

57:15.866 --> 57:17.234
you're gonna have to
pull your weight

57:17.367 --> 57:18.736
a little more around here.

57:18.869 --> 57:21.906
And one thing that we thought
would help you contribute--

57:22.039 --> 57:24.374
would be easy,
wouldn't be hard to do--

57:24.509 --> 57:27.745
is to help Ray bring his kids
back and forth to school

57:27.878 --> 57:30.748
when he can't do it
because of work.

57:30.881 --> 57:32.817
Like now.

57:32.950 --> 57:34.251
Like today.

57:34.384 --> 57:35.886
(chuckles)

57:36.020 --> 57:38.222
You're joking, right?

57:38.355 --> 57:41.058
You want me to take
your kid to school?

57:41.191 --> 57:43.093
The kid that I tattooed?

57:43.227 --> 57:46.430
I got two kids.
The other one's seven.

57:46.564 --> 57:48.232
You're gonna make me
babysit your kids?

57:48.365 --> 57:51.101
Do-- I'm on-- I do drugs.

57:51.235 --> 57:53.871
Well, looks like you're walking.

57:54.004 --> 57:55.873
And thank you.

57:56.006 --> 57:58.876
I'm not cool with
any of this, okay?

57:59.009 --> 58:00.778
And-and where do you
expect me to live?

58:00.911 --> 58:02.279
And w-with what money?
(stammers)

58:02.412 --> 58:04.114
You know I'm a fucking bum,
right?

58:04.248 --> 58:06.350
Yo, this is fucked up!
Seriously.

58:06.483 --> 58:10.487
Especially after last night,
all that bonding boy bullshit.

58:11.488 --> 58:12.523
You're full of shit, man.

58:12.657 --> 58:14.458
You're a fucking liar.

58:14.592 --> 58:17.294
I'm gonna go walk your kids.

58:17.427 --> 58:19.697
No, I'm not fucking
letting you take 'em.

58:19.830 --> 58:21.932
Fuck you.
Who the fuck are you?

58:22.066 --> 58:23.634
SCOTT: Yeah, I-I agree
with you completely.

58:23.768 --> 58:25.302
Why-- 'cause that--
It was Ray's idea.

58:25.435 --> 58:26.871
I don't think I should be
taking them, either.

58:27.004 --> 58:28.038
I agree with you.

58:30.407 --> 58:32.042
Are you a weirdo?

58:32.176 --> 58:33.443
Oh, the weirdest.

58:33.578 --> 58:35.045
Nobody's weirder than me.

58:35.179 --> 58:37.447
See, a weirdo wouldn't say that.

58:37.582 --> 58:39.416
A weirdo would deny it.

58:39.550 --> 58:42.753
So, do I have to take 'em or...?

58:42.887 --> 58:45.155
(exhales sharply)

58:45.289 --> 58:46.223
Yes.

58:46.356 --> 58:48.392
God, no.

58:48.525 --> 58:50.227
I mean, (scoffs)
Ray was supposed to do it.

58:50.360 --> 58:51.629
I can't fucking do it.

58:51.762 --> 58:53.263
Their schools start
half an hour apart

58:53.397 --> 58:54.799
on the other side of town.

58:54.932 --> 58:56.601
(Gina sighs)

58:59.069 --> 59:02.673
So, your mom is banging my ex?

59:02.807 --> 59:04.809
Yeah, I'm not thrilled
about it, either.

59:04.942 --> 59:07.477
Yeah, well, you shouldn't be.

59:07.612 --> 59:09.647
-(sighs)
-Harold. Kelly.

59:09.780 --> 59:11.181
Come here. Come here.

59:11.315 --> 59:14.184
There's something,
something kind of fun.

59:14.318 --> 59:15.620
Come here. Come here.

59:15.753 --> 59:17.421
-Oh, hey, man.
-(clears throat)

59:17.554 --> 59:20.591
So, this is Harold,
and this is Kelly.

59:20.725 --> 59:23.160
And, uh, this is...

59:24.228 --> 59:25.763
Scott.

59:25.896 --> 59:27.932
Scott. He's gonna be
taking care of you.

59:28.065 --> 59:30.134
-Okay? It...
-Nice to meet you, Scott.

59:30.267 --> 59:32.336
Hi, Harold.
It's nice to meet you.

59:32.469 --> 59:34.104
For the very first time.

59:34.238 --> 59:35.940
GINA:
If he does anything weird,

59:36.073 --> 59:37.274
you tell me.

59:37.407 --> 59:40.310
Even if he tells you
not to tell me, you tell me.

59:40.444 --> 59:44.348
I'm pretty sure he's not weird,
but I could be wrong.

59:44.481 --> 59:45.449
'Kay?

59:45.582 --> 59:46.617
-Love you.
-Okay.

59:46.751 --> 59:47.685
-Love you, Mom.
-Seriously.

59:47.818 --> 59:49.119
Love you, Mom. Bye.

59:49.253 --> 59:50.320
Pay attention.

59:50.454 --> 59:52.690
Got it.

59:52.823 --> 59:54.825
GINA:
Hold both their hands!

59:58.128 --> 01:00:00.030
Thank you.

01:00:01.098 --> 01:00:02.466
Look both ways. Look both ways!

01:00:02.599 --> 01:00:04.534
(quietly):
Tell her to stop.

01:00:04.669 --> 01:00:07.037
God!

01:00:07.171 --> 01:00:09.173
So, w-what do you like
to do, Harold?

01:00:09.306 --> 01:00:11.541
I like superheroes.

01:00:11.676 --> 01:00:13.410
Well, so does everybody.

01:00:13.543 --> 01:00:15.245
No, I make up my own.

01:00:15.379 --> 01:00:17.081
Oh, yeah? What kind?

01:00:17.214 --> 01:00:18.582
Ice Flash.

01:00:18.716 --> 01:00:20.851
What does he do?

01:00:20.985 --> 01:00:25.222
He freezes stuff
and shoots ice at people.

01:00:26.556 --> 01:00:28.192
Oh, well, that's not gonna work.

01:00:28.325 --> 01:00:29.459
Why not?

01:00:29.593 --> 01:00:31.361
I could just use a hair dryer
and ruin him.

01:00:31.495 --> 01:00:33.030
(stammers)
Keep thinking, though.

01:00:33.163 --> 01:00:35.032
What do you got?
What do you like to do?

01:00:35.165 --> 01:00:37.067
-I like to sing.
-You do?

01:00:37.201 --> 01:00:39.069
Could-could you sing for me?

01:00:39.203 --> 01:00:40.537
Sure.

01:00:40.671 --> 01:00:44.341
* Oh, what a beautiful morning *

01:00:44.474 --> 01:00:45.342
Yes.

01:00:45.475 --> 01:00:48.345
* Oh, what a beautiful day *

01:00:48.478 --> 01:00:49.346
All right.

01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:53.884
* I've got a wonderful feeling *

01:00:54.018 --> 01:00:57.521
* Everything's going my way. *

01:00:57.654 --> 01:00:59.223
That shit was dope.
High five.

01:00:59.356 --> 01:01:00.490
She's a good singer.

01:01:00.624 --> 01:01:02.727
I don't agree with
the sentiment of the song,

01:01:02.860 --> 01:01:04.428
but it was really great.

01:01:04.561 --> 01:01:07.597
Anyway, have a great day
at school.

01:01:07.732 --> 01:01:10.200
Uh... I hope it's not shitty,

01:01:10.334 --> 01:01:13.137
and, um, yeah, give your,
uh, sister a kiss goodbye.

01:01:13.270 --> 01:01:15.773
-We don't do that.
-Just do it.

01:01:19.710 --> 01:01:21.611
-See? Wasn't that nice?
-(school bell ringing)

01:01:21.746 --> 01:01:23.613
Now, if she dies tomorrow,
you'll remember that,

01:01:23.748 --> 01:01:24.982
that you kissed her goodbye.

01:01:25.115 --> 01:01:26.650
Have a good day at school.

01:01:26.784 --> 01:01:29.286
-Later, man.
-Pay attention.

01:01:29.419 --> 01:01:31.722
-Why would I die?
-I don't know.

01:01:31.856 --> 01:01:33.290
You never know
what's gonna happen.

01:01:33.423 --> 01:01:35.059
Think you're immortal?

01:01:38.095 --> 01:01:39.764
This. It's this one.

01:01:39.897 --> 01:01:41.766
Okay. All right.

01:01:41.899 --> 01:01:43.600
(kids chattering)

01:01:43.734 --> 01:01:45.836
Well, have a good day, okay?

01:01:45.970 --> 01:01:47.471
-KELLY: Okay.
-I'll see you soon, I guess.

01:01:47.604 --> 01:01:49.639
-Can-can I help you?
-Oh, hi.

01:01:49.774 --> 01:01:51.008
I'm-I'm Ray's friend.

01:01:51.141 --> 01:01:53.377
I was just here
to bring her here.

01:01:54.912 --> 01:01:57.181
-You-you know Ray?
-I know Ray a little bit.

01:01:57.314 --> 01:01:59.583
He's kind of, like,
banging my mom. (chuckles)

01:01:59.716 --> 01:02:01.151
-(chuckles)
-So, yeah, I'm just, you know,

01:02:01.285 --> 01:02:02.186
just dropping her off.

01:02:02.319 --> 01:02:04.188
Did you sign in at the office?

01:02:04.321 --> 01:02:06.290
No. I didn't even know
you had an office.

01:02:06.423 --> 01:02:08.325
Okay, um...

01:02:08.458 --> 01:02:09.860
Kelly? You okay?

01:02:09.994 --> 01:02:11.295
Yeah.

01:02:11.428 --> 01:02:12.662
-You sure?
-Yeah.

01:02:12.797 --> 01:02:14.264
You know you can tell me.

01:02:14.398 --> 01:02:16.133
I'm okay.

01:02:16.266 --> 01:02:17.534
Do you know him?

01:02:17.667 --> 01:02:18.635
Yeah, kind of.

01:02:18.769 --> 01:02:20.704
He's a new friend.

01:02:20.838 --> 01:02:22.773
Okay.

01:02:22.907 --> 01:02:24.842
Oh, I trained her in the car.
She's not gonna break.

01:02:24.975 --> 01:02:26.176
-(chuckles nervously)
-I'm just kidding.

01:02:26.310 --> 01:02:27.845
It's, uh...
I'm not gonna hurt her.

01:02:27.978 --> 01:02:29.613
Um, but have a great day.
I just...

01:02:29.746 --> 01:02:32.216
No, uh, actually, could you,
uh, set up the paints?

01:02:32.349 --> 01:02:33.650
-No.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:02:33.784 --> 01:02:35.019
-Uh, and just wash
these brushes. -No.

01:02:35.152 --> 01:02:36.286
-Thank you so much.
-No. No.

01:02:36.420 --> 01:02:38.388
-Thank you!
-No.

01:02:38.522 --> 01:02:40.524
(hard rock music playing)

01:02:45.262 --> 01:02:46.763
(tattoo gun buzzing)

01:02:56.640 --> 01:02:58.575
Did-did you happen
to get a chance

01:02:58.708 --> 01:03:01.145
-to take a look at the, uh...
-Yeah, I looked at your book.

01:03:01.278 --> 01:03:04.314
I mean, I drew like that, too,
when I was 14.

01:03:04.448 --> 01:03:06.884
From what I saw, you don't
really have the basics,

01:03:07.017 --> 01:03:08.819
so you got to figure that out.

01:03:08.953 --> 01:03:10.254
Well, yeah, that's why I'm here.

01:03:10.387 --> 01:03:12.589
I mean, I was hoping
I can learn from you.

01:03:12.722 --> 01:03:15.025
Right, well, um,
you'd be my apprentice.

01:03:15.159 --> 01:03:16.526
Uh, you'll be a slave
to the shop.

01:03:16.660 --> 01:03:19.229
-Hey, man. As long as I get
to tattoo people, right? -No.

01:03:19.363 --> 01:03:21.866
Never. Until I say.

01:03:21.999 --> 01:03:24.334
Uh, you'll be sterilizing
needles, washing my car,

01:03:24.468 --> 01:03:25.535
taking the trash out.

01:03:25.669 --> 01:03:27.237
